============================================================
PART 3: D^6 TRUE DEGREE-2 WALSH
============================================================
D^6 = (sum S_l sigma_l)^6. Degree-2 at {a,b}:
Patterns with n_a odd, n_b odd, sum=6:
  (5,1,0): 6*Sa^5*Sb
  (1,5,0): 6*Sa*Sb^5
  (3,3,0): 20*Sa^3*Sb^3
  (3,1,2c): 60*Sa^3*Sb*Sc^2
  (1,3,2c): 60*Sa*Sb^3*Sc^2
  (1,1,4c): 30*Sa*Sb*Sc^4
  (1,1,2c,2d): 180*Sa*Sb*Sc^2*Sd^2

But (1,1,2c,2d) with c!=d is degree-4 Walsh! (4 distinct sigma vars)
True degree-2 excludes (1,1,2c,2d) cross-terms.

